/*
:name: if_expr_rhs
:type: equiv
:verilog_top: if_expr_rhs.ifsel
:pyrope_top: if_expr_rhs.ifsel
*/

// if/elif/else used as an RHS *expression value* (not statement form). Each
// arm's value is hoisted to a result tmp; the output is a real mux. Regression
// guard for two miscompiles:
//   o,p: the historical "unhandled node type 'ref' -> output wired to nil"
//        (that residue is now a hard tolg error).
//   q:   the elif-chain-with-comptime-const-else fold-to-the-else-constant bug
//        (`q` used to compile to constant 0, dropping the c/d arms) — the
//        comptime arm store to the result tmp was dropped + the tmp kept the
//        else const. Fixed in constprop (keep arm stores under uncertainty) +
//        symbol_table (invalidate the result tmp on arm exit).
pub comb ifsel(c:bool, d:bool, a:u8, b:u8) -> (o:u8, p:u8, q:u8) {
  o = if c { a } else { b }
  p = if c { b } else { a }
  q = if c { a } elif d { b } else { 0 }
}
